<H3> <TI>   SADF Expresses Concerns NPKF Capabilities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SADF Expresses Concerns NPKF Capabilities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2304080694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2304080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The South African Army has become the latest 
institution to express serious concerns about the capabilities 
of the National Peace Keeping Force [NPKF]. The chief of the 
Army, General Hattingh Pretorius, said in Heidelberg in the 
Transvaal that the Defense Force was lately perceived as being 
the only organization that could ensure stability and protect 
the country from anarchy and chaos. He said the image of the 
SADF [South African Defense Force] was now more positive than 
that of any other security force. 

</TEXT>

