<H3> <TI>   Finland's President To Attend Inauguration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finland's President To Attend Inauguration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2204094494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0901 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2204094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E van Wyk] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria April 22 SAPA -- Finland's newly elected 
President Mr Martti Ahtisaari plans to attend the inauguration 
of South Africa's new president in Pretoria on May 10, the 
Finland Embassy said on Friday. Mr Ahtisaari, a former career 
diplomat and a former director-general of the Finnish Foreign 
Affairs Ministry, was for years closely connected with southern 
Africa. "His role in the developments leading to Namibia's 
independence was a particularly difficult one," the embassy 
statement said. Mr Ahtisaari was at the time the special 
representative of the United Nations secretary-general for 
Namibia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-1234 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr079_c_94068" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Britain's Prince Philip To Attend Inauguration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Britain's Prince Philip To Attend Inauguration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2104193494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2104193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Queen Elizabeth will be represented by her consort, 
Prince Philip, at the swearing in of South Africa's new 
president on the 10th of next month, ending a 47-year-old break 
in official visits by Britain's royal family. This was announce 
by Buckingham palace in London today. In 1947 King George VI 
visited South Africa with his consort and daughters, Elizabeth, 
now queen, and Margaret. 

</TEXT>

