<H3> <TI>   No Role in Election Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Role in Election Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2204165794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2204165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Peacekeeping Force will not play any 
part in election security. This role will be performed 
exclusively by the police and defense force. Major General Gert 
Opperman of the SADF [South African Defense Force] said that 
members of the SADF would be deployed near voting stations, 
while the SAP [South African Police] would be responsible for 
the immediate security of the voting stations. 

</TEXT>

