<F P=101> Zambia </F>
<H3> <TI>   120 ANC Members Arrive for Military Training </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    120 ANC Members Arrive for Military Training </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2504164394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2504164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One-hundred-and-twenty members of the ANC have 
arrived in Zambia to undergo military training. An ANC 
spokesman said the training aimed at preparing the members for 
integration into a national defense force after the elections. 
The cost of the training will be carried by the Zambian 
Government. 

</TEXT>

