<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Liberia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ECOMOG Troops `Ambushed' in Tubmanburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ECOMOG Troops `Ambushed' in Tubmanburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2504184494 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2504184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States 
Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] force carrying reinforcements to 
quell the factional fighting in ULIMO [United Liberation 
Movement for Democracy in Liberia] has been ambushed in 
Tubmanburg, Bomi County. The force, which was carrying troops to 
the troubled headquarters of ULIMO to stop the fighting between 
Alhaji Koromah's Mandingo and rival Roosevelt Johnson's Krahn 
supporters, was reportedly hit by rockets on its way to 
Tubmanburg. ECOMOG has also suffered casualty in the Tubmanburg 
incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

