<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deadline set by the government for the surrender 
of firearms expired yesterday. No statement has so far been 
issued. Earlier, the government warned all groups in possession 
of firearms, whether lawfully or unlawfully, that the Army and 
the security committees will be forced to search for firearms if 
they are not surrendered. A government announcement called on 
armed groups to stop shooting and on the Army to maintain 
discipline and to use weapons for self defense. 
  Speaking to reporters, Defense Minister Gedeon Fyiroko 
disclosed that the seizure of arms would take place in all parts 
of the country, that is the municipalities, divisions, and 
regions. Meanwhile, our reporter in Karuzi region has reported 
that two soldiers were shot and injured by unknown assailants. 

</TEXT>

