<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IEC Considering Extending Voting Hours </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IEC Considering Extending Voting Hours </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2604094594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0837 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2604094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg April 26 SAPA -- The Independent 
Electoral Commission [IEC] says the decision on whether or not 
to keep voting stations open after 7PM on the three voting days 
will be entirely up to the presiding officer overseeing the 
process. 
  An IEC statement said on Tuesday [26 April] issues such as 
the safety of the area after dark would be considered. The 
IEC's major concern was to allow every eligible voter an 
opportunity to cast his or her ballot. "Every effort to achieve 
that will be undertaken and all kinds of measures will be 
employed," the statement said. 
  Additional electoral officials would be brought in to staff 
the voting stations should the need arise, or if the presiding 
officer requested it. Mobile voting stations could also be used. 
  The commission called on voters to exercise "patience, 
understanding and co-operation in this historic process". 

</TEXT>

