<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi Contacts IEC on `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buthelezi Contacts IEC on `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2604140094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1310 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2604140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durban April 26 SAPA -- Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
President Mangosuthu Buthelezi said on Tuesday [26 April] he had 
been in contact with Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] 
Chairman Judge Johann Kriegler about the crisis in the voting 
process in Natal, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] 
radio news reported. He said numerous calls had been received 
from IFP voters in many areas complaining about voting 
procedures. 
  Mr Peter Miller of the IFP's electoral office in 
Pietermaritzburg said an IFP member, who had refused to accept a 
ballot paper without the party sticker, had been told to sign it 
at the bottom. 
  Only when he refused to do that, was he given a proper 
ballot 
paper with an IFP sticker. 

</TEXT>

