<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Temporary Voter Cards Available in KwaZulu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Temporary Voter Cards Available in KwaZulu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2604115894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1114 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2604115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by C. Govender] </F>
  [Text] Durban April 26 SAPA -- Special arrangements have 
been made for the issuing of temporary voters cards (TVCs) 
during the three-day election period, KwaZulu government 
spokesman T C Memela announced on Tuesday. He said TVC's would 
be attainable at all KwaZulu polling booths. KwaZulu 
citizenship certificates could also be used as identity 
documents, said Mr Memela. Persons in possession of such a 
certificate need not apply for a voter card, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

