<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dirk van Zyl] </F>
  [Text] Cape Town April 26 SAPA -- By mid-morning there had 
been no security problems at any of the voting points for 
special votes in the Western Cape, an Independent Electoral 
Commission spokesman said on Tuesday [26 April]. "The security 
forces have not reported any major problems," he said. An 
administrative hitch in the Mitchell's Plain area -- where 
ballots had not reached the right destinations -- had been 
sorted out, he added. And a claim that the African Christian 
Democratic Party had distributed pamphlets on Tuesday at the 
Buffeljags Prison at Swellendam, in contravention of the ruling 
that all electioneering cease on Monday, was being investigated. 

</TEXT>

