<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network 
in English at 1535 GMT on 23 April broadcasts the following 
advertisement: First, a slogan sung by several voices: "Join us 
and build a better future." Then follows a voice reading the 
following: "The great thing about a multiparty democracy is that 
one party cannot just do whatever it likes, because the others 
keep an eye on it. Look, we did have opposition parties in the 
past but, well, maybe they were too weak to do anything, you 
know. This time I'm making sure we get a better life. I'm 
voting with my head, not my heart. I'm voting for the new 
National Party." The advertisement is followed by the voices 
singing: "Be sure of a better life for you." 
  At the beginning and end of the advertisement an announcer 
says: "This political advertisement was paid for by the party." 

