<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Eighteen people have been injured, at least six of 
them seriously, in this morning's explosion at Jan Smuts Airport 
in Johannesburg. The blast occurred on the second floor of the 
international arrivals hall, causing extensive damage to the 
interior of the building. Several windows were blown out and 
the ceiling collapsed. 

</TEXT>

