<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi Casts Vote at Umlazi Polling Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buthelezi Casts Vote at Umlazi Polling Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2704055194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0531 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2704055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durban April 27 SAPA -- Shortly before 7.30AM 
KwaZulu Chief Minister and Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] leader 
Mangosuthu Buthelezi cast his vote at an Umlazi polling station. 
Few voters at the polling station knew about the IFP leader's 
unannounced arrival and there were only about 50 voters at the 
station. Just before Mr Buthelezi's arrival at Umlazi the 
ballot papers and necessary IFP stickers had been delivered. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

