<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Viljoen Casts Vote, Urges End to Bomb Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Viljoen Casts Vote, Urges End to Bomb Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2704091894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0904 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2704091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E. van Wyk] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria April 27 SAPA -- Freedom Front leader 
Constand Viljoen was accompanied by a large group of former 
police and defence force generals when he cast his vote for his 
party at the Voortrekkerhoogte Town Hall on Wednesday [27 
April]. Gen Viljoen told the media that he condemned the Jan 
Smuts Airport bomb blast and urged those responsible to stop the 
bombings and rather vote for the Freedom Front to strengthen the 
party's hand in future negotiations. Gen Viljoen described his 
voting in the country's first ever democratic election as the 
"last possible peaceful way to achieve the goal of 
self-determination". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

